NewsNight anchor Vuyo Mvoko got more information from the South African National Defence Force spokesperson Brigadier-General Mafi Mgobozi. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A shooting has taken place outside 1 Military Hospital in Pretoria. South African National Defence Force spokesperson, Brigadier-General Mafi Mgobozi, confirmed that foreign nationals travelling in a BMW opened fire at a Mercedez Benz outside the hospital which led to the SANDF guards to return fire. "Two vehicles, a BMW and a Mercedes Benz were involved in an altercation. The guys in the BMW opened fire at those in the Mercedes. The Mercedes drove towards the hospital which is when our guards opened fire at the BMW because they continued shooting in the area where our guards are." No patients or bystanders or SANDF members wereÂ hurt during the shootout but one of the suspects was wounded. "One of the foreign nationals was wounded in the hand," said Mgobozi. Mgobozi says emergency services are on the scene.